1
00:00:03,333 --> 00:00:05,866
[ZORZAL] In the great name of
Zorzal El Caesar,

2
00:00:05,966 --> 00:00:10,633
[ZORZAL] I declare... the
foundation of the office of
Crown Prince!

3
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:14,166
[ZORZAL] As of this moment,
the Empire is under my command!

4
00:00:14,266 --> 00:00:16,300
[ZORZAL] And our Empire is
vulnerable.

5
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:21,566
[ZORZAL] After suffering great
losses in so many battles, the
Senate chooses not to fight.

6
00:00:21,666 --> 00:00:23,566
[ZORZAL] Instead wants to
surrender to our foes,

7
00:00:23,666 --> 00:00:26,366
[ZORZAL] They wish to sell out
the freedom and dignity

8
00:00:26,466 --> 00:00:28,433
of each and every one of you!

9
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:30,533
[ZORZAL] All to protect only
themselves!

10
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:33,466
[PEOPLE] <outrage>

11
00:00:33,566 --> 00:00:36,400
[ZORZAL] Their true cowardice
and complacency is showing.

12
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:40,200
We won't entrust our nation to
weakness. No!

13
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:42,666
This realm is ours!

14
00:00:42,766 --> 00:00:47,000
[ZORZAL] You are the strong and
noble people of this Empire.

15
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,466
[ZORZAL] You are the chosen ones
that have

16
00:00:49,566 --> 00:00:53,200
successfully ruled this realm
for over 600 years.

17
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:56,100
[ZORZAL] Now is the time for us
to come together,

18
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:58,633
We must show what we are capable
of.

19
00:00:58,733 --> 00:01:01,400
[ZORZAL] It is time to overcome
the turmoil around us,

20
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:04,500
And grow our Empire's strength
and power.

21
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,600
[ZORZAL] Let us all gather
around our flag,

22
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:09,433
[ZORZAL] And let us all make
history together!

23
00:01:09,533 --> 00:01:11,466


24
00:01:11,566 --> 00:01:17,600
[CROWD] Zorzal, Zorzal, Zorzal,
Zorzal, Zorzal, Zorzal, Zorzal

25
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:34,766
<Chanting, hollering>

26
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:40,000
[ZORZAL] And so... now it's time

27
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:43,066
[ZORZAL] To begin the war with
Japan

28
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:25,866
[IMAZU] Well... it looks like
Prince Zorzal's coup d'etat was
successful. Over.

29
00:03:25,966 --> 00:03:29,533
[NYUTABARU] Yes. That's right...
And the Empire's under martial
law,

30
00:03:29,633 --> 00:03:32,366
[NYUTABARU] So leaving the
premises is restricted. Over.

31
00:03:32,466 --> 00:03:34,500
[IMAZU] Is the Vice Minister
safe?

32
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,933
[NYUTABARU] Yes. Jade Palace is
protected under the agreement.

33
00:03:37,033 --> 00:03:39,400
[NYUTABARU] there should be no
need to worry.

34
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,233
[IMAZU] We are in no position to
let our guard down.

35
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:45,066
See if you can find out
the condition of the Emperor.
Over.

36
00:03:45,166 --> 00:03:46,766
[NYUTABARU] Will do. Over and
out.

37
00:03:49,733 --> 00:03:51,800
[PINA] Did you learn the
whereabouts of Lelei?

38
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:55,966
[GREY] Yes. Apparently, she is
trying to become a master of the
magic arts.

39
00:03:56,066 --> 00:03:57,466
[PINA] She's in Rondel?

40
00:03:57,566 --> 00:03:59,833
[ZORZAL] Pina.

41
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:01,233
[PINA] Brother!

42
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:03,666
[ZORZAL] That girl is a hero of
the entire Empire.

43
00:04:03,766 --> 00:04:05,066
Bring her back safe and sound.

44
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:06,433
[GREY] Of course, your Highness.

45
00:04:06,533 --> 00:04:08,666
[PINA] Zorzal. May I ask you
something?

46
00:04:08,766 --> 00:04:12,366
[ZORZAL] What is it now?
It may not look it,
but I am a busy man.

47
00:04:12,466 --> 00:04:14,433
[PINA] Would you mind telling me
why you're placing

48
00:04:14,533 --> 00:04:17,033
the pro‐peace representatives
under house arrest?

49
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:20,266
<annoyed tsk>
[ZORZAL] Oh yes of course that.

50
00:04:20,366 --> 00:04:21,766
[PINA] What did you say?

51
00:04:21,866 --> 00:04:23,266
[ZORZAL] The
representatives‐for‐peace

52
00:04:23,366 --> 00:04:25,433
have been receiving bribes and
other gifts from Japan.

53
00:04:25,533 --> 00:04:27,966
[PINA] That's absurd! Do you
have any evidence of this?!

54
00:04:28,066 --> 00:04:29,933
[ZORZAL] Oh I will find proof
eventually.

55
00:04:30,033 --> 00:04:32,466
A definitive source that cannot
be rebuked.

56
00:04:34,466 --> 00:04:37,300
[PINA] Then tell me. What is it
you're planning to do?

57
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:39,366
[ZORZAL] Nothing at all...

58
00:04:39,466 --> 00:04:41,233
In the absence of the Emperor...

59
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:44,533
[ZORZAL] I am simply to carry
out my Princely duty as I see
fit.

60
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:47,033
[ZORZAL] But if you stand in my
way...

61
00:04:47,133 --> 00:04:49,300
[PINA] Will you make a prisoner
out of me as well?

62
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,033
[ZORZAL] That shouldn't be
necessary.

63
00:04:51,133 --> 00:04:54,500
I need you to act as an
intermediary peace negotiator
with Japan.

64
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,566
[PINA] You're continuing with
the negotiations?

65
00:04:56,666 --> 00:05:00,700
[ZORZAL] Of course I am.
But without... resorting to a
defeatist mentality,

66
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:05,466
[ZORZAL] and after taking
measures to ensure our victory
that is. Understand?

67
00:05:05,566 --> 00:05:08,433
[HELM] Um Prince Zorzal, we have
come at your request.

68
00:05:08,533 --> 00:05:11,433
[ZORZAL] These are the men
I have appointed as my generals.

69
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:14,033
[ZORZAL] I'm sure you know a few
of them.

70
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:15,100
[PINA] I do.

71
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,233
[ZORZAL] Very well...

72
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:18,066
I called you for a simple
reason.

73
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:20,333
[ZORZAL] Gentlemen do you
have a plan in place...

74
00:05:20,433 --> 00:05:21,966
to fight the upcoming battle.

75
00:05:22,066 --> 00:05:23,866
[HELM] Our enemy is extremely
powerful, sire.

76
00:05:23,966 --> 00:05:26,733
If we approach it as a
traditional fight, we'll surely
lose.

77
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:29,266
[HELM] We will need to adopt a
more sinister course.

78
00:05:29,366 --> 00:05:31,566
[ZORZAL] Really now. A sinister
course?

79
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:32,500
[HELM] Yes.

80
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,266
We will gather goblins,

81
00:05:34,366 --> 00:05:36,266
[HELM] And have them attack the
villages near Alnus.

82
00:05:36,366 --> 00:05:37,266
[PINA] What?!
[HELM] And have them attack the
villages near Alnus.

83
00:05:37,366 --> 00:05:38,500
[ZORZAL] Don't you think

84
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,633
that would provoke them.

85
00:05:39,733 --> 00:05:41,333
Our enemy will seek
retaliation and invade us.

86
00:05:41,433 --> 00:05:43,233
[KALASTA] There's no need to
worry about that.

87
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:46,300
This will be the work of
a group of freelance thieves
and bandits.

88
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,066
[HELM] And we can take it even
further.

89
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,233
Our soldiers could disguise
themselves to look like

90
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,466
the enemy when they are
attacking the villages.

91
00:05:52,566 --> 00:05:56,100
[ZORZAL] Ha Ha. So we make our
enemy look like the bad guys.

92
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,533
[HELM] That way their reputation
will be compromised..

93
00:05:58,633 --> 00:06:00,500
and our people will turn against
them.

94
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,266
[PINA] You should be ashamed of
yourselves!

95
00:06:02,366 --> 00:06:05,000
You are supposed to be a
dignified soldier of the
Empire?!

96
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:06,900
[HELM] It is the only way we can
fight them.

97
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,733
We can't possibly win otherwise,
Princess Pina.

98
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:10,900
I think you know that.

99
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,366
[ZORZAL] Very good

100
00:06:12,466 --> 00:06:15,200
[ZORZAL] Proceed with the plan.
[PINA] But you can't!

101
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:16,833
[HELM] We'll start preparations
right away.

102
00:06:16,933 --> 00:06:18,733
<react>

103
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:21,633
[PINA] Helm... It was a mistake
to have negotiated your release.

104
00:06:21,733 --> 00:06:23,500
[HELM] I have no words to
describe how grateful I am

105
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,666
for your kindness, Princess...
as my former superior.

106
00:06:25,766 --> 00:06:30,766
[HELM] Now leave everything to
us, and get yourself some rest.

107
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,433
[PINA] Diavo! Brother!

108
00:06:36,533 --> 00:06:39,600
[PINA] What's going on?!.. What
is this, where are you going?

109
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,700
[DIAVO] Just keep moving.

110
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,533
[PINA] You answer me right now!

111
00:06:43,633 --> 00:06:45,666
[DIAVO] I'm getting as far as I
can from this place.

112
00:06:45,766 --> 00:06:49,900
[PINA] But you can't!
You must help me stop Zorzal
from destroying everything.

113
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,900
You have responsibilities
as a member of the imperial
family

114
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,800
[DIAVO] I am carrying out
my responsibilities.

115
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:59,066
I shall stop our deranged
brother by gathering forces
from foreign nations.

116
00:06:59,166 --> 00:07:01,066
[PINA] What? You're inviting
them into the Empire?!

117
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:03,466
[DIAVO] I'm afraid there's no
other way.

118
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,833
[DIAVO] Get out of the road you
idiot!

119
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:10,233
[PINA] Diavo. Please think about
this.

120
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:13,800
[PINA] If you do this our land
and people will be taken away.

121
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,600
[PINA] There will be no Empire
left.

122
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:18,633
[DIAVO] And if Zorzal's
dictatorship continues.

123
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:20,300
The empire will fall anyway.

124
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,500
[DIAVO] That bigot needs to be
forced into listening

125
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,433
through a demonstration of
strength.

126
00:07:24,533 --> 00:07:26,133
[DIAVO] That's all I can tell
you now get out of the way!

127
00:07:26,233 --> 00:07:28,600
[PINA] I will not!
[DIAVO] Move or I'll run you
over!

128
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,800
[PINA] If it's for the sake of
the Empire...

129
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:32,166
I don't care what happens to me!

130
00:07:32,266 --> 00:07:35,366
[DIAVO] Oh, grow up! Hyaa!!
[PINA] Stop! Diavo!

131
00:07:35,466 --> 00:07:39,666
[DIAVO] Ideals aren't going to
help you survive, Pina!

132
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:41,566
<react>

133
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:44,866
[LELEI] I would like to
introduce you to her properly.

134
00:07:44,966 --> 00:07:46,333
This is Mimoza.

135
00:07:46,433 --> 00:07:48,766
[LELEI] She's a wizard and a
great sage.

136
00:07:48,866 --> 00:07:50,800
She's one of the elders in
Rondel.

137
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:52,500
[MIMOZA] It is nice to meet you.

138
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:55,066
So how long has it been, Rory?
[ITAMI] Huh?

139
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:57,066
[TUKA] You know each other?
[LELEI] I had no idea.

140
00:07:57,166 --> 00:07:59,866
<laugher> [MIMOZA] We traveled
together awhile back.

141
00:07:59,966 --> 00:08:03,966
[MIMOZA] About 50 years ago,
doesn't that sound right? Rory?

142
00:08:04,066 --> 00:08:06,600
[RORY] Mimoza... You're so...
old.

143
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:11,033
[MIMOZA] Oh my. Yes, I am. I've
earned some wrinkles haven't I?

144
00:08:11,133 --> 00:08:13,200
[MIMOZA] Sure you're jealous.

145
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:14,633
[MIMOZA] So I heard that you
went on

146
00:08:14,733 --> 00:08:16,866
a little holiday to the other
side of the Gate.

147
00:08:16,966 --> 00:08:18,600
[MIMOZA] What was it like over
there?

148
00:08:19,566 --> 00:08:21,200
[RORY] Hmm... It was just
lovely...

149
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:23,600
the streets were nice and
impeccably clean.

150
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:26,066
[TUKA] Every shop had a wide
variety of products.

151
00:08:26,166 --> 00:08:27,700
And looked like they were doing
well.

152
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:31,800
[LELEI] I especially liked their
wonderful bookstores.

153
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:35,133
[ITAMI] Lelei?
[LELEI] They had books from
every field you can think of.

154
00:08:35,233 --> 00:08:37,800
Sold at very affordable prices
even for the commoners.

155
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:39,533
[MIMOZA] The commoners could buy
books?

156
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:42,933
[LELEI] In Japan, the ability
to publish books is very
accessible.

157
00:08:43,033 --> 00:08:46,000
[LELEI] There was even a market
with books by amateurs for sale.

158
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:50,600
[MIMOZA] Oh dear dear. That
would be incredible to have
books for everyone.

159
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:53,066
[ARPEGGIO] Oh no no no!

160
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:56,300
That's one thing that can never
ever happen! Never ever ever
ever...

161
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,933
Never ever.

162
00:08:59,033 --> 00:09:01,900
If my magic encyclopedia that I
copied by hand night after night

163
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,400
after night were to go down in
price...

164
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,266
[ITAMI] What is wrong with her?
[Arpeggio rants]

165
00:09:05,366 --> 00:09:06,533
[LELEI] One of Arpeggio's
jobs is a scribe writing books.

166
00:09:06,633 --> 00:09:07,733
She's upset how cheap
they are to make.

167
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:08,600
And how easy her job is.

168
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:11,600
[Arpeggio continues]

169
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:13,933
[MIMOZA] Her specialty
is in mineral magic,

170
00:09:14,033 --> 00:09:16,233
which can be rather pricey
in order to maintain.

171
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:17,500
...AND if book prices go
down on top of that...

172
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:20,033
Ugh... How will I pay
for food and rent?

173
00:09:20,133 --> 00:09:23,233
I'll get kicked out if I miss
another payment...

174
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:25,033
[LELEI] Now don't you worry.

175
00:09:25,133 --> 00:09:27,533
I'm sure the price won't drop
right away.

176
00:09:27,633 --> 00:09:29,700
[LELEI] That would be far into
the future.

177
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,200
[ARPEGGIO] Sure about that?

178
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:33,766
Welllll why didn't you say so,
you trying to scare me?!

179
00:09:33,866 --> 00:09:35,166
What. Is. Your. Deal?!

180
00:09:35,266 --> 00:09:39,033
Anyway. Like I said...
she's a mineral specialist.

181
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:41,000
[MIMOZA] Which means she could
really be of help

182
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,466
for your resource survey.

183
00:09:42,566 --> 00:09:44,700
[ITAMI] That sounds great, would
you be up for that?

184
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:49,566
[ARPEGGIO] Well sure... I would
be happy to help you.

185
00:09:49,666 --> 00:09:50,766
<giggle>

186
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,233
[MIMOZA] Are you curious?

187
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:56,566
You seem to be very interested
in that picture.

188
00:09:56,666 --> 00:09:58,066
[RORY] Oh no not really.

189
00:09:58,166 --> 00:10:01,500
Glad you came, even if you were
just tagging along.

190
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,166
I've been wanting to give you an
answer

191
00:10:03,266 --> 00:10:04,166
to
the homework you gave me.

192
00:10:04,266 --> 00:10:05,533
[ITAMI] Homework?

193
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:06,733
[RORY] That's correct.

194
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:08,166
I gave her a problem to resolve

195
00:10:08,266 --> 00:10:09,766
before we parted ways.

196
00:10:09,866 --> 00:10:11,466
[RORY] To answer why there are

197
00:10:11,566 --> 00:10:13,900
such varied species in this
world.

198
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,533
[ITAMI] Is there an answer to
that?

199
00:10:15,633 --> 00:10:17,133
[RORY] Of course there is.

200
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:18,766
[MIMOZA] It is because...

201
00:10:18,866 --> 00:10:21,733
[MIMOZA] Of the Gate. Oh dear.

202
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,000
[MIMOZA] The creation legend for
the elves

203
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:33,066
begins with a man and woman

204
00:10:33,166 --> 00:10:37,233
...who were led by a God to the
Forest of Origin.

205
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:40,100
[MIMOZA] Now, elves are spread
throughout the realm,

206
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:43,766
but every tribe has their own
version of the origin story.

207
00:10:43,866 --> 00:10:45,666
[MIMOZA] When you ask the
location

208
00:10:45,766 --> 00:10:47,000
of the Forest of Origin,

209
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:48,500
...the elves in the
north point to the south,

210
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,433
...and the elves in the
south point to the north.

211
00:10:50,533 --> 00:10:53,600
And it all leads to one
location.

212
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:55,033
[ITAMI] So... Alnus.

213
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:56,200
[MIMOZA] That's correct.

214
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:59,066
[LELEI] So all elves come from
Alnus?

215
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:00,933
[MIMOZA] Oh well not just elves.

216
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:03,766
All sorts of species across the
region

217
00:11:03,866 --> 00:11:06,000
claim Alnus as their home.

218
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,500
[ARPEGGIO] And what do you think
about that, Master?

219
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:10,033
[MIMOZA] I've traveled this
world my entire life

220
00:11:10,133 --> 00:11:11,866
and my research has born much
fruit.

221
00:11:11,966 --> 00:11:13,733
[RORY] And tell me, what is the
answer

222
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,333
you were finally able to
discover?

223
